lineItems.description: Clean Inverter panel
Men, material & tools have been cleared from area
Check inverter fans are working properly
Caution boards / barricade removed
Clean inverter fans & filter
Checked the working & adjacent areas and found no smoke & fire while completing and also after job completion.
Check for any unusual smell which indicates overheating
Area has been cleaned (cotton waste, scraps, electrical wire etc.,) and inspected. Scaffold / ladders removed
Check for any noise and vibration
All Panel Boards are properly Locked
Check Inverter control Supply (UPS)- P-N,P-E, & N-E
All Fire Extinguishers & Buckets properly placed
Check Inverter Auxiliary Supply - P-N,P-E, & N-E
Check Intake Air Temparature - Inverter
Check Intake Air Pressure- AFU
Check the working of display and LED indicators
Ensure proper sealing of Inverter hot air outlet duct.
Clean the Inverter station
Check for water/liquid ingress.
Physically inspect the inverter station internal and external including proper fixing of door, grills, louvers
Check for alarms, LCD status, abnormalities, LED indicators.
Check for water/liquid ingress. (Monthly in monsoon season and Quarterly for rest of Year)
Check for abnormal noise or vibrations.
Check the status of the door and door lock.
Check the DC bus bar there is no mark of spark.
Check Surge protection device
Check the cables are in good condition.
Verify the indication of fuse blown in DC line and associate micro switch and AC side fuse
Clean the AC breaker
Check the AC breaker ON / OFF
